@patcaseybmx always made me smile, laugh and feel grateful for every moment, always living every second out to its fullest potential.  He was wise beyond his years, knew what he wanted, married his beautiful wife @chasecasey at a young age adding two amazing blessed kids @reidcaseybmx and Taytum to the family.  It's hard to find balance in the world, I might have not been around the Casey family all the time, but I didn't need to be to see his dedication as a dad and husband.  Family is always number one to Pat, but on top of his family values, he's stayed on top of the action sports world forever one of the greatest bmx athletes to exist.  I looked at old text threads between Pat/Me and attached a couple of them, in 2012 Pat asked me if he could get some Ethika briefs, you're telling me young superstar PAT CASEY is asking me to rock my brand "Heck to the Yea" I was to the moon and back.  Another thing about Pat is he always looked out for his friends as they were coming up, Pat connected me in 2013 to young legends @kevinPeraza @seanricany and so many more, bmx is a family and everyone in it means so much to me.  Most importantly our text that goes back celebrating Reid being born, then Taytum and then Pat's encouragement as my wife was about to give birth to our daughter Rilyn, these talks and memories hold forever close to me.  My love, heart, prayers and support are forever with the Casey family, I'm tearing as I type this, my heart is so broken right now like all that know the Casey family, at the same time my heart is so full to have known and shared so many great memories with such a legend and his family.  As we celebrate Pat's life, this a Reminder to Breathe, Pat lived his life to the fullest and will be really upset looking down if we don't do the same…🙏❤️

So I live in Cali, land in Maryland and head straight to @travispastrana’s house AKA Pastranaland at the beginning of its legacy in the early 2000s

I’m the marketing & athlete manager for No Fear. Travis was 1 of our athletes we signed for apparel at 12 years old. Although I grew up riding/racing moto, at this point I’m way more on the business side than trying to be a racer..

As I’m going down the big hill leading to his foam pit I see him standing on top of the ramp with his thumbs up & that timeless Pastrana smile, which normally means he’s up to something

I’ve got my backpack on, haven’t stretched, ride time’s on the low & the first words out of Trav’s mouth are “I just did a double backflip into the foam pit, it’s easier than a single, when you see the blue sky, look back.. you got this”

Gullible me is optimistic and believes Trav who’s one heck of a salesman. This is all at the beginning of the backflip era and of course Pastrana was already thinking doubles

Within minutes Trav made sure I was suited up. To my recollection, I was ready to hit the ramp within 15 minutes. For whatever reason I was confident but the nerves and excitement were rumbling through my body

I listened to Travis & it was now go time. I couldn’t believe the feeling, remember seeing that blue sky Travis mentioned and was in shock as I landed at the end of the foam pit with no room to go, about 3-5 feet from pulling off a @street_bike_tommy and missing the foam pit

So here’s the kicker…

In the midst of this unbelievable feeling I look up to Travis still standing tall with this interesting look of astonishment. 

His eyes bulging like Nemo and as all these emotions are racing through me, I’m confused so with the adrenaline hitting hard I ask Travis “WHAT’S UP WITH THAT LOOK?”

He’s like “DUDE you just landed a double backflip! I haven’t been able to pull it off yet and I’ve been trying for days”

My confidence landing the double exceeded my skills as I went for my first backflip on a big bike. 

Travis’ response says it all 😂

Props to Trav for always showing us that we’re capable of more than we think we are…

“Everything I do is for the 17 year old version of myself” @virgilabloh ❤️🙏

Every single day I wake up thinking about that restless, ambitious 17 year old version of me. 

Their raw energy, undying passion, and heavy belief that they can change the world. 

It's the late nights, the early mornings, the moments of doubt followed by breakthroughs… 

We owe it to our younger selves to honor those dreams, to keep pushing, to never settle. 

Virgil’s famous line is a powerful reminder for us all. Never lose sight of the fire that started it all. Show that kid inside that their dreams weren't just dreams…

They were blueprints 🫡

Self awareness isn’t just a buzzword, it’s the foundation of growth 💯

If you’re facing something and there’s even a whisper in your heart that YOU might be the problem, don’t shy away from it…

Dive deep, confront it, and work through that truth

Once you recognize it, you’ve already taken the first major step towards turning things around. Remember, accountability is where real progress starts. 

As the weekend approaches, consider this your reminder to breathe, smile, and transform your thoughts, even if it’s a little uncomfortable at first. What’s waiting for you on the other side always outweighs any temporary discomfort 🔥

After over 20 years of ideation & innovation in the brief game, couldn’t be more thrilled to continue taking it to new levels with @themendid 

I’ve always been a fabric guy and heavily inspired by that OG @nba mesh and its use across street culture

Our vision to launch with the fabric we did came in 2 parts:

1) It was the softest premium fabric I’ve felt in ages and had an incredible 4-way stretch with a durable elasticity that holds true to form

2) The material blend along with the mesh made for a crazy breathable performance fabric that when combined with Mendid’s fit allowed you to go from your daily charge to properly kitted up for wherever the night takes you

At the end of the day our biggest strength is that we believe in people

Mendid is your reminder to breathe, push boundaries, and live your authentic truth

In 2012 I went with my gut, personally copped a $1,500 ticket to Miami, inviting @dirtshark and @mitchcbdg6464 from @monsterenergy
 I only had a day to find 2 bikes for my boys @meekmill and @chinobraxton to hop on and show the Monster execs in person what the bike life’s all about, with the goal of getting them a deal

Ended up negotiating to use 2 new KXs & paid to rent out a go kart track for them to do some work. The rest was history…

Timing on my side, ended up in the studio with Meek, capturing him in the moment as he recorded what ultimately became one of his biggest hits, Dreams & Nightmares… All blessings

God’s used me to connect culture and I always listen…

“Hold up, wait a minute, y’all thought I was finished?” 😉

You already know this trip wouldn’t have been complete without some work in the streets, and because of that the dirt came natural

Grateful to still be using bikes to cross cultures after all these years…

Messaging aside, my vision for weaving the mesh into our launch was to crush the false belief that mesh is “only for sport” by fusing it with our patented design pattern and creating the most breathable, comfortable at all times brief I’ve ever worn in my 20+ years of developing underwear

Listen, my life has been completely transformed because of the mentors who took the time to guide me, believe in me, and put me in a position to see the greatness woven within myself, and I’m eternally grateful for that...

Mendid? That’s my way of giving back and paying it forward. We’re taking that gratitude, that appreciation, and weaving it into one grateful thread that connects us all

We live in a world where too many people are trying to keep the gates closed, trying to hoard success, tools and opportunity for themselves...

Mendid is here to rip those gates right off their hinges

Because EVERYONE has the potential to uncover the greatness woven within themselves and become more than what others or the system may have lead them to believe

We’re here to remind you of that, to provide inspiration to sharpen your own sword and make it happen

Life & becoming Mendid is an ongoing work in progress and you have to start somewhere.

Just know you’re not alone… Let’s be on the mend together
